You should know that I share your distaste for body horror skips, so you had an uphill battle with me here.

There are three components to this SCP, mechanically, that I gleaned from reading it — I might be missing something.

Christian Paulman, a barista/author
The book/fad diet
The creatures themselves


I have to admit that, while I see the explicit connection between these three features (Paulman gets dumped by a girl/struggles with mental illness, writes a fad diet book, fad diet book makes people spoopy), I have to admit the article isn't communicating the implict reason why to me properly. And I'm also afraid that I kind of don't like the  sort of story, admittedly, which is all I'm really gleaning from this backstory.

-1, but I hope you know it comes from a place of deep respect for your work. Positives: Excellent, breezy technical writing and good image choice.







